00:18:22,669 --> 00:18:23,668
- come on! Cut it out!

460
00:18:23,703 --> 00:18:24,836
What's going on?
What's going on?

461
00:18:24,871 --> 00:18:28,139
- Oh, just your father and
bill Ryan going at it again.

462
00:18:28,174 --> 00:18:29,407
- If you two don't knock it off,

463
00:18:29,442 --> 00:18:32,610
the committee will disqualify
both of you from the contest.

464
00:18:33,480 --> 00:18:35,746
- But this is
Christmas, gentlemen.

465
00:18:35,782 --> 00:18:37,849
This is the season of forgiving.

466
00:18:37,884 --> 00:18:40,451
- Bill, come on, come on.

467
00:18:44,958 --> 00:18:46,524
- What if Dante sees you?

468
00:18:46,559 --> 00:18:49,527
Do you want him to see his
Nono making a fool of himself

469
00:18:49,562 --> 00:18:51,496
in front of everyone
in the town?

470
00:19:04,711 --> 00:19:07,545
- No-no, who was that man
you were arguing with?

471
00:19:07,580 --> 00:19:08,513
- Nobody.

472
00:19:08,548 --> 00:19:10,081
- Mm. They used to be friends.

473
00:19:10,116 --> 00:19:12,016
- Good friends,
once upon a time.

474
00:19:12,051 --> 00:19:15,286
- Started a holiday decorating
company in college together.

475
00:19:15,321 --> 00:19:17,588
- Yeah and kept it going
after they graduated.

476
00:19:17,624 --> 00:19:19,690
They called it making
spirits bright,

477
00:19:19,726 --> 00:19:22,360
was a nice little business
for them during the holidays.

478
00:19:22,395 --> 00:19:24,428
- We even used to spend
Christmases together.

479
00:19:24,464 --> 00:19:26,230
- What happened then?

480
00:19:26,266 --> 00:19:27,431
- Well...

481
00:19:27,467 --> 00:19:30,234
He kept pestering me
to decorate faster

482
00:19:30,270 --> 00:19:32,170
so we could get more clients.

483
00:19:33,273 --> 00:19:37,475
And all I really cared about
was doing the quality of work.

484
00:19:37,510 --> 00:19:39,277
He cared about the money.

485
00:19:39,312 --> 00:19:41,979
So we got into an
argument and he kicked me

486
00:19:42,015 --> 00:19:43,047
out of the company.

487
00:19:43,082 --> 00:19:45,383
- Yes. I broke up the company.

488
00:19:45,418 --> 00:19:47,919
Because frank told
me that I was greedy,

489
00:19:48,755 --> 00:19:51,422
that I put quantity
over quality.

490
00:19:51,457 --> 00:19:53,424
Just because I wanted to
make a few extra dollars

491
00:19:53,459 --> 00:19:54,559
doing something we both loved,

492
00:19:54,594 --> 00:19:57,595
doesn't make my reasons for
doing it any less noble.

493
00:19:57,630 --> 00:19:59,797
- They were a great partnership.

494
00:19:59,832 --> 00:20:01,966
- We brought out the
best of each other...

495
00:20:03,469 --> 00:20:04,735
For a time.

496
00:20:04,771 --> 00:20:06,237
You know, he would
draw up the designs

497
00:20:06,272 --> 00:20:09,106
and I'd put a plan
together and execute them.

498
00:20:09,142 --> 00:20:11,475
But when he insulted
me, that was it.

499
00:20:11,511 --> 00:20:12,944
That was the end of our business

500
00:20:12,979 --> 00:20:15,112
and the end of our friendship.

501
00:20:15,148 --> 00:20:17,949
- And that's when grandpa
opened up the furniture store

502
00:20:17,984 --> 00:20:20,685
and turned making spirits
bright into deck the halls.

503
00:20:20,720 --> 00:20:22,787
- Can't you just
apologize and make up?

504
00:20:22,822 --> 00:20:24,322
You two were so close.

505
00:20:24,357 --> 00:20:27,091
- Apologize to him
after what he said?

506
00:20:27,126 --> 00:20:28,859
He should be apologizing to me.

507
00:20:28,895 --> 00:20:31,028
- It's a shame what
happened between you two

508
00:20:31,064 --> 00:20:32,630
is all I'm saying.

509
00:20:32,665 --> 00:20:34,165
- No, the only shame here is
that frank was never admit

510
00:20:34,200 --> 00:20:35,766
he was wrong.

511
00:20:35,802 --> 00:20:36,734
Now come on.

