00:42:37,956 --> 00:42:40,023
- Oh, it's just pigheadedness.

1025
00:42:40,058 --> 00:42:41,691
- It's like bill and the store.

1026
00:42:41,726 --> 00:42:43,393
He put money before good sense.

1027
00:42:43,428 --> 00:42:45,695
We never should've opened
the other location.

1028
00:42:46,565 --> 00:42:47,697
Carla knows.

1029
00:42:47,732 --> 00:42:48,898
- Oh, wow.

1030
00:42:48,934 --> 00:42:52,235
I guess everyone's up to speed
on all the family secrets.

1031
00:42:52,270 --> 00:42:53,736
- Yeah, with one exception.

1032
00:42:54,606 --> 00:42:57,206
What are you two
doing out altogether?

1033
00:42:57,242 --> 00:42:58,041
- Aah.

1034
00:42:58,076 --> 00:42:59,275
- Are you a date?

1035
00:42:59,311 --> 00:43:01,444
- What? No.
- No, no.

1036
00:43:01,479 --> 00:43:05,882
We, we just bumped into each
other and then we saw...

1037
00:43:05,917 --> 00:43:06,749
Not a date.

1038
00:43:06,785 --> 00:43:07,884
- Yeah, no.

1039
00:43:07,919 --> 00:43:09,285
But we should get out of here.

1040
00:43:09,321 --> 00:43:10,119
- Yes.

1041
00:43:10,155 --> 00:43:11,321
Let's leave you to it.

1042
00:43:11,356 --> 00:43:12,288
- Let you finish your...

1043
00:43:12,324 --> 00:43:14,524
- And don't worry, your
secret's safe with us.

1044
00:43:18,263 --> 00:43:22,065
- They came in together and
now they're leaving together.

1045
00:43:22,100 --> 00:43:23,499
- Seems like a date to me.

1046
00:43:23,535 --> 00:43:24,734
- Oh yes it does.

1047
00:43:24,769 --> 00:43:26,903
(Carla and Arlene laughing)

1048
00:43:26,938 --> 00:43:28,504
- I can't believe it.

1049
00:43:28,540 --> 00:43:30,807
They kept their friendship
a secret for all these years

1050
00:43:30,842 --> 00:43:32,809
without anybody knowing it.

1051
00:43:32,844 --> 00:43:34,110
- Yeah.

1052
00:43:34,145 --> 00:43:35,278
- I didn't think my
mother had it in her.

1053
00:43:35,313 --> 00:43:36,212
- Yeah.

1054
00:43:39,351 --> 00:43:41,017
- What, you're thinking about
your dad and the stores,

1055
00:43:41,052 --> 00:43:43,353
aren't you?

1056
00:43:43,388 --> 00:43:44,821
You know, maybe I can help.

1057
00:43:46,191 --> 00:43:48,024
Put that MBA to use.

1058
00:43:48,059 --> 00:43:50,326
Sometimes it's good to have
an outside pair of eyes

1059
00:43:50,362 --> 00:43:51,794
to take a look.

1060
00:43:51,830 --> 00:43:54,263
- That is a very,
very nice offer,

1061
00:43:54,299 --> 00:43:57,000
but my dad's head would
explode if he knew a Scotto

1062
00:43:57,035 --> 00:43:58,801
was looking at
the company books.

1063
00:44:00,338 --> 00:44:02,438
- Well...

1064
00:44:02,474 --> 00:44:05,308
Maybe we don't tell them.

1065
00:44:06,211 --> 00:44:08,845
If our mothers can pull
off a little subterfuge,

1066
00:44:08,880 --> 00:44:10,413
why can't you and I?

1067
00:44:11,916 --> 00:44:14,050
- Meet me at the
store in the morning?

1068
00:44:14,085 --> 00:44:14,984
- It's a da-

1069
00:44:16,554 --> 00:44:18,454
an appointment, an appointment.

1070
00:44:20,558 --> 00:44:21,357
- An appointment?

1071
00:44:21,393 --> 00:44:22,058
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

1072
00:44:22,093 --> 00:44:26,295
("deck the halls" instrumental)

1073
00:44:29,834 --> 00:44:31,401
- is this all of it?

1074
00:44:31,436 --> 00:44:33,136
- What, you want
there to be more?

1075
00:44:34,539 --> 00:44:36,873
I'll give it to my father,
he is well organized.

1076
00:44:36,908 --> 00:44:38,975
- Well, let's get through
as much of it as we can

1077
00:44:39,010 --> 00:44:41,177
before we have to get
back to the contest.

1078
00:44:44,349 --> 00:44:47,250
(gentle piano music)

1079
00:44:47,285 --> 00:44:50,353
come on, grab the
spreadsheet, dig in.

1080
00:44:50,388 --> 00:44:52,355
- Right.

1081
00:44:52,390 --> 00:44:55,491
(gentle piano music)

1082
00:45:02,701 --> 00:45:05,868
(birds chirping)

1083
00:45:05,904 --> 00:45:06,803
- what's wrong?

1084
00:45:08,006 --> 00:45:11,074
- I think I figured out how to
make those icicles look like

1085
00:45:11,109 --> 00:45:12,775
they're melting.

1086
00:45:12,811 --> 00:45:13,710
But...

1087
00:45:15,113 --> 00:45:16,446
- But what?

1088
00:45:16,481 --> 00:45:17,780
- Means, we're going to
have to take them down

1089
00:45:17,816 --> 00:45:19,248
and redo them.

1090
00:45:19,284 --> 00:45:21,384
- No. Pop, we don't
have time for that.

1091
00:45:21,419 --> 00:45:22,618
- No, we can do it.

1092
00:45:22,654 --> 00:45:23,786
It'll only takes
a couple of hours.

1093
00:45:23,822 --> 00:45:27,390
This needs to be perfect.
It needs to be my best work.

1094
00:45:27,425 --> 00:45:30,693
It's what the people expect.
It's what I expect of myself.

1095
00:45:30,729 --> 00:45:31,728
Nothing less.

1096
00:45:32,664 --> 00:45:35,431
(curious music)

1097
00:45:41,473 --> 00:45:43,372
- don't be too hard
on yourself, dad.

1098
00:45:43,408 --> 00:45:45,208
Still got one more
day to make it sing.

1099
00:45:45,243 --> 00:45:46,809
Plus we only have to be good
enough to get in the finals,

1100
00:45:46,845 --> 00:45:48,077
right?

1101
00:45:48,113 --> 00:45:49,278
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

1102
00:45:58,923 --> 00:46:00,990
- Well that doesn't
look like much.

1103
00:46:01,025 --> 00:46:03,793
- Oh! (laughing)

1104
00:46:03,828 --> 00:46:06,229
- well, that's because they
haven't turned it on yet.

1105
00:46:08,099 --> 00:46:10,500
- And that's it for
today, everyone!

1106
00:46:10,535 --> 00:46:13,736
We'll be picking the two
finalists tomorrow evening.

1107
00:46:13,772 --> 00:46:16,472
So make your last day count.

1108
00:46:16,508 --> 00:46:18,040
See y'all in the morning!

1109
00:46:19,677 --> 00:46:20,676
- Woo!

1110
00:46:20,712 --> 00:46:24,013
Haha! Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.

1111
00:46:24,048 --> 00:46:24,847
Yes!

1112
00:46:24,883 --> 00:46:26,015
(techno music blaring)

1113
00:46:26,050 --> 00:46:26,949
ha!

1114
00:46:26,985 --> 00:46:28,117
Woo!

1115
00:46:28,153 --> 00:46:29,085
- Okay.

1116
00:46:29,120 --> 00:46:30,787
- What'd I tell you
about the cross beams?

1117
00:46:30,822 --> 00:46:32,789
You didn't want to have
them, but I was right again.

1118
00:46:32,824 --> 00:46:33,790
Wade wins again!

1119
00:46:35,460 --> 00:46:37,426
- Still think it
doesn't look like much?

1120
00:46:40,131 --> 00:46:43,266
(gentle piano music)

1121
00:46:47,906 --> 00:46:48,771
- you're up early.

1122
00:46:48,807 --> 00:46:50,306
- Yeah.

1123
00:46:50,341 --> 00:46:52,308
A friend just asked me to
go through their company's

1124
00:46:52,343 --> 00:46:55,444
financials to see if I
could diagnose any problems,

1125
00:46:55,480 --> 00:46:57,446
coming up with a few ideas.

1126
00:46:57,482 --> 00:46:59,148
It's been kind of fun actually.

1127
00:47:00,118 --> 00:47:02,952
You know, I feel like
I can genuinely help.

1128
00:47:02,987 --> 00:47:03,519
It feels good.

1129
00:47:03,555 --> 00:47:05,321
- Anthony, that's great.

1130
00:47:05,356 --> 00:47:06,689
- Yeah.

1131
00:47:06,724 --> 00:47:08,391
- Good to see that
glimmer in your eye again.

1132
00:47:08,426 --> 00:47:09,892
- Thank you.

1133
00:47:09,928 --> 00:47:10,827
- This last year, I've
seen how hard you've been

1134
00:47:10,862 --> 00:47:11,928
on yourself.

1135
00:47:12,997 --> 00:47:14,831
I was starting to worry
that maybe you were taking

1136
00:47:14,866 --> 00:47:16,299
after your old man.

1137
00:47:16,334 --> 00:47:18,634
- (laughs) what do
you mean by that?

1138
00:47:18,670 --> 00:47:21,370
- Nothing. Nevermind.

1139
00:47:21,406 --> 00:47:22,672
- No. Hey pop, come on.

1140
00:47:22,707 --> 00:47:24,307
You can't just come...

1141
00:47:24,342 --> 00:47:26,843
I mean, take a seat. Talk
to me. What do you mean?

1142
00:47:32,183 --> 00:47:34,383
- Those first bright
nights contests,

1143
00:47:35,253 --> 00:47:37,587
every time I won, first
thought I had was,

1144
00:47:37,622 --> 00:47:40,189
"how am I going to
top myself again?"

1145
00:47:40,225 --> 00:47:42,191
I got so in my head about it,

1146
00:47:42,227 --> 00:47:44,126
it's why I couldn't
finish that year.

1147
00:47:45,196 --> 00:47:48,698
I stopped competing completely
because I was embarrassed.

1148
00:47:50,068 --> 00:47:52,235
I thought this year was
going to be different,

1149
00:47:52,270 --> 00:47:55,238
but we are one day away and
I can't make heads or tails

1150
00:47:55,273 --> 00:47:57,640
of what I want to do or
what I'm trying to do.

1151
00:47:59,043 --> 00:48:01,244
I'm worried we're not
going to finish again.

1152
00:48:02,146 --> 00:48:03,045
- Pop.

1153
00:48:04,482 --> 00:48:07,016
Come on. We're going
to finish, okay?

1154
00:48:08,052 --> 00:48:10,419
I promise, whatever it
takes we're going to finish.

1155
00:48:13,258 --> 00:48:14,090
Okay?

1156
00:48:18,062 --> 00:48:20,696
(bill singing)

1157
00:48:28,239 --> 00:48:29,872
- morning, dad.

1158
00:48:29,908 --> 00:48:30,907
- Oh, hey kiddo.

1159
00:48:34,178 --> 00:48:35,244
Everything all right?

1160
00:48:36,114 --> 00:48:37,013
- Yeah.

1161
00:48:37,048 --> 00:48:38,648
Sarah and I are supposed
to go to this party.

1162
00:48:38,683 --> 00:48:40,283
It's something that
should be good for us,

1163
00:48:40,318 --> 00:48:42,118
for our business, but...

1164
00:48:42,153 --> 00:48:43,753
- You'd rather not.

1165
00:48:44,789 --> 00:48:47,490
- The last few weeks we
haven't felt like partners.

1166
00:48:47,525 --> 00:48:49,492
It's been the Sarah show.

1167
00:48:49,527 --> 00:48:52,428
I can't tell if it's
because she's right

1168
00:48:52,463 --> 00:48:54,130
and my design sense is way off,

1169
00:48:54,165 --> 00:48:56,499
or if she just decided
that her opinion matters

1170
00:48:56,534 --> 00:48:57,433
more than mine.

1171
00:48:59,137 --> 00:49:01,637
- Well, now I understand
why you're so hesitant to

1172
00:49:02,840 --> 00:49:04,907
give up your creative input.

1173
00:49:04,943 --> 00:49:06,509
- I know how much this
contest means to you.

1174
00:49:06,544 --> 00:49:08,077
I didn't want to
lead you astray.

1175
00:49:08,112 --> 00:49:11,247
- (laughs) that's the last
thing I'd ever worry about,

1176
00:49:11,282 --> 00:49:12,581
grace.

1177
00:49:12,617 --> 00:49:15,418
- I guess I'm just
nervous to talk with Sarah

1178
00:49:15,453 --> 00:49:16,585
about all of this,

1179
00:49:16,621 --> 00:49:19,021
because I know there's a chance
that this could be the end

1180
00:49:19,057 --> 00:49:22,091
of everything we built together,
even worse, our friendship.

1181
00:49:24,062 --> 00:49:24,994
- All right.

1182
00:49:25,029 --> 00:49:29,098
It's your voice, your
creativity. (laughs)

1183
00:49:29,133 --> 00:49:31,534
that's what makes
you so special.

1184
00:49:31,569 --> 00:49:34,303
You can't let anyone tap
it down or drown it out.

1185
00:49:34,339 --> 00:49:37,006
A real partner will value
all of your opinions,

1186
00:49:38,509 --> 00:49:40,943
even if sometimes
it may be wrong.

1187
00:49:40,979 --> 00:49:42,378
You know?

1188
00:49:42,413 --> 00:49:43,946
Speaking of which,

1189
00:49:43,982 --> 00:49:47,616
if you have any miracle
fixes for this deck house,

1190
00:49:48,553 --> 00:49:50,052
now's the time.

1191
00:49:50,088 --> 00:49:51,220
- It looks good, dad.

1192
00:49:51,255 --> 00:49:54,190
- Good's not going to cut
it where wade is concerned.

1193
00:49:55,426 --> 00:49:56,359
- Don't lose hope.

1194
00:49:57,395 --> 00:49:58,828
- I'm not.

1195
00:49:58,863 --> 00:50:01,197
I'm just looking at the
reality of the things.

1196
00:50:03,835 --> 00:50:06,702
Anyway, I should get ready,
it's going to be a long day.

1197
00:50:08,406 --> 00:50:09,839
Chin up.

1198
00:50:09,874 --> 00:50:10,773
- Thanks.

1199
00:50:11,542 --> 00:50:14,377
(cheerful music)

1200
00:50:29,961 --> 00:50:33,262
("deck the halls" tune)

1201
00:50:37,969 --> 00:50:40,336
- all right, load it out.

1202
00:50:41,139 --> 00:50:42,038
Easy does it.

1203
00:50:52,650 --> 00:50:55,551
- Everyone's acting like
we already lost weight.

1204
00:50:55,586 --> 00:50:57,086
- Well, yeah, but I mean...

1205
00:50:59,857 --> 00:51:01,290
Step into my office.

1206
00:51:05,196 --> 00:51:06,829
(grace sighs)

1207
00:51:06,864 --> 00:51:09,965
look, based on where both
of our houses are at,

1208
00:51:10,001 --> 00:51:12,601
neither one of them is going
to take us into the finals.

1209
00:51:13,738 --> 00:51:16,138
- Yeah, but we just need one
of us to get to the finals,

1210
00:51:16,174 --> 00:51:17,673
and then we've got a shot.

1211
00:51:17,708 --> 00:51:19,175
- True.

1212
00:51:19,210 --> 00:51:21,911
- I have an idea of how
we could do this, but...

1213
00:51:21,946 --> 00:51:22,812
- What?

1214
00:51:28,319 --> 00:51:28,984
Wow, that...

1215
00:51:29,020 --> 00:51:31,220
That's beautiful. You drew that?

1216
00:51:32,390 --> 00:51:34,490
But that's way more
than a day's work.

1217
00:51:34,525 --> 00:51:36,292
- Yeah, for three people it is,

1218
00:51:36,327 --> 00:51:38,894
but with seven, we
could pull it off.

1219
00:51:40,298 --> 00:51:42,431
- Where you going to get
these extra four people?

1220
00:51:44,635 --> 00:51:47,670
(mischievous tones)

1221
00:51:48,806 --> 00:51:49,705
no.

1222
00:51:49,740 --> 00:51:51,207
My family?

1223
00:51:51,242 --> 00:51:52,475
- Well, you just said that
neither one of our houses

1224
00:51:52,510 --> 00:51:54,276
are good enough to
make it to the finals.

1225
00:51:54,312 --> 00:51:56,645
But if our families
work together,

1226
00:51:56,681 --> 00:51:59,115
maybe we could bring out
the best in each other.

1227
00:52:00,751 --> 00:52:03,319
- Or if the last 20 years
have been any indication,

1228
00:52:03,354 --> 00:52:05,020
maybe we'll bring out the worst.

1229
00:52:05,957 --> 00:52:08,624
- Did you bump your head
on the ice or something?

1230
00:52:08,659 --> 00:52:11,393
I would rather hang
up the lights for good

1231
00:52:11,429 --> 00:52:13,062
than work with bill Ryan again.

1232
00:52:13,097 --> 00:52:14,563
- You know what?

1233
00:52:14,599 --> 00:52:16,465
If partnering up with him
is a more painful thought

1234
00:52:16,501 --> 00:52:19,001
than letting wade and
his carnival light show

1235
00:52:19,036 --> 00:52:22,271
walk away with the
title, then fine, don't.

1236
00:52:23,341 --> 00:52:25,574
But if decorating means
as much as I know it does

1237
00:52:25,610 --> 00:52:29,044
to you, then temporarily
putting aside your pride,

1238
00:52:30,014 --> 00:52:31,380
it's a small price to pay.

1239
00:52:33,551 --> 00:52:36,051
Look, I said we'd do
whatever it takes to finish,

1240
00:52:37,188 --> 00:52:38,521
whatever it takes.

1241
00:52:40,024 --> 00:52:41,223
This is what it takes.

1242
00:52:43,461 --> 00:52:44,827
- Well, what does bill say?

1243
00:52:45,630 --> 00:52:47,096
- Bill?

1244
00:52:47,131 --> 00:52:48,063
He's...

1245
00:52:48,099 --> 00:52:49,031
- Open to it.

1246
00:52:50,134 --> 00:52:51,333
- Really?

1247
00:52:51,369 --> 00:52:53,035
- Well he didn't say no.

1248
00:52:53,070 --> 00:52:53,903
- Hm.

1249
00:52:55,072 --> 00:52:56,138
The kids are right.

1250
00:52:56,174 --> 00:52:57,940
There's no way our two
houses are going to make it

1251
00:52:57,975 --> 00:52:58,974
to the finals.

1252
00:52:59,911 --> 00:53:01,110
- Okay.

1253
00:53:01,145 --> 00:53:03,679
So we work together,
temporarily,

1254
00:53:03,714 --> 00:53:05,581
just so we have a better chance.

1255
00:53:05,616 --> 00:53:06,282
- All right.

1256
00:53:06,317 --> 00:53:08,517
But if that happens and we win,

1257
00:53:08,553 --> 00:53:11,520
we split the contract and
the money, 50/50, okay?

1258
00:53:17,161 --> 00:53:18,561
- [frank] let's go to work.

1259
00:53:18,596 --> 00:53:19,962
- [bill] let's.

1260
00:53:19,997 --> 00:53:23,032
- You and the scottos want
to partner up. Really?

1261
00:53:23,067 --> 00:53:24,233
- Yeah, exactly.

1262
00:53:24,268 --> 00:53:27,870
We want to join forces and work
on just this house together.

1263
00:53:27,905 --> 00:53:29,772
- Well, there's nothing in the
competition agreement saying

1264
00:53:29,807 --> 00:53:32,141
that you can't decorate
one house together,

1265
00:53:32,176 --> 00:53:34,310
but I do want to run
it by the other teams.

1266
00:53:34,345 --> 00:53:35,711
- Oh, we asked.

1267
00:53:35,746 --> 00:53:36,979
Mistletoe designs
already signed off on it.

1268
00:53:37,014 --> 00:53:37,646
- What about wade?

1269
00:53:37,682 --> 00:53:39,615
- They have my full support.

1270
00:53:41,018 --> 00:53:41,984
Can't wait to see
what rabbit hole

1271
00:53:42,019 --> 00:53:44,386
their collective
imaginations take them down.

1272
00:53:44,422 --> 00:53:46,622
- Since their team now
consists of seven people,

1273
00:53:46,657 --> 00:53:49,725
I think it only fair that
mistletoe designs and glowscapes

1274
00:53:49,760 --> 00:53:50,659
add to theirs.

1275
00:53:50,695 --> 00:53:52,661
- Mm. I feel good about
our current number.

1276
00:53:52,697 --> 00:53:55,231
More people would
